e International Court of Justice referred to the line determined by the 1900 Honduras-Nicaragua Mixed Boundary Commission and advised that some tripartite resolution among El Salvador, Honduras and Nicaragua likely would be required.\nBULLET::::- El Salvador has an embassy in Tegucigalpa and consulates-general in Choluteca and San Pedro Sula.\nBULLET::::- Honduras has an embassy in San Salvador.\n valign=\"top\"\n1838See El Salvador–Mexico relations\n\nDiplomatic relations between Mexico and El Salvador were established in 1838.\nBULLET::::- Mexico has an embassy in San Salvador.\nBULLET::::- El Salvador has an embassy in Mexico City and consulates-general in Acayucan, Monterrey, Tapachula and San Luis Potosí and consular offices in Arriaga, Comitán and in Tenosique.\n valign=\"top\"\n\nBULLET::::- El Salvador has an embassy in Managua.\nBULLET::::- Nicaragua has an embassy in San Salvador.\n valign=\"top\"\n\nBULLET::::- El Salvador has an embassy in Panama City.\nBULLET::::- Panama has an embassy in San Salvador.\n valign=\"top\"\n\nBULLET::::- El Salvador is accredited to Paraguay from its embassy in Montevideo, Uruguay.\nBULLET::::- Paraguay is accredited to El Salvador from its embassy in Bogotá, Colombia.\n valign=\"top\"\n\nBULLET::::- El Salvador has an embassy in Lima.\nBULLET::::- Peru has an embassy in San Salvador.\n valign=\"top\"\n\nBULLET::::- El Salvador has an embassy in Port of Spain.\nBULLET::::- Trinidad and Tobago is accredited to El Salvador from its embassy in San José, Costa Rica.\n valign=\"top\"\nSee El Salvador–United States relations\n\nU.S. policy towards the country promotes the strengthening of El Salvador's democratic institutions, rule of law, judicial reform, and civilian police; national reconciliation and reconstruction; and economic opportunity and growth. El Salvador has been a committed member of the coalition of nations fighting against terrorism and has sent 10 rotations of troops to support the Iraq War.\n\nBULLET::::- El Sa