sy in Addis Ababa.\n valign=\"top\"\n\nBULLET::::- Ethiopia is accredited to Romania from its Permanent Mission in Geneva, Switzerland.\nBULLET::::- Romania has an embassy in Addis Ababa.\nBULLET::::- Ethiopian Ministry of Foreign Affairs about bilateral relations with Romania\n valign=\"top\"\n1943-4-21\nBULLET::::- Russia has an embassy in Addis Ababa.\nBULLET::::- Ethiopia has an embassy in Moscow. The Ethiopian ambassador to Russia is also accredited to Armenia, Azerbaijan, Belarus, Georgia, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, Moldova, Tajikistan, Turkmenistan, Ukraine, and Uzbekistan.\nBULLET::::- The history of this relationship has its origins in the 19th century. Russia supplied the mountain guns the Ethiopian army used in the Battle of Adwa.\nBULLET::::- More recently, the Soviet Union was a major source of military and economic aid under the Derg and during the People's Democratic Republic of Ethiopia.\nBULLET::::- See also Alexander Bulatovich\nBULLET::::- Relations are somewhat unsure owing to Russia's close ties with Ethiopia's neighboring rival, Sudan.\n valign=\"top\"\n1952\nBULLET::::- Serbia has an embassy in Addis Ababa.\nBULLET::::- Ethiopia is accredited Serbia from its embassy in Rome, Italy.\nBULLET::::- Ethiopia is a strong advocate for Serbia on the issue of Kosovo.\nBULLET::::- The first vessel in the Ethiopian Navy was a gift from Yugoslavia.\nBULLET::::- The Serbian embassy is the former villa of Yugoslav President Josip Broz Tito, which was given as a gift by Haile Selassie\nBULLET::::- On 27 January 2012, after traveling to Addis Ababa in order to reaffirm Ethiopia's stance on Kosovo regarding Serbia, Vuk Jeremić and Haile Mariam signed a memorandum of understanding between the two nations' ministries of foreign affairs.\n valign=\"top\"\n\nBULLET::::- Ethiopia is accredited to Spain from its embassy in Paris, France.\nBULLET::::- Spain has an embassy in Addis Ababa.\n valign=\"top\"\nSee Ethiopia–Sweden relations\n\nBULLET::::- Ethiopia has an emba